        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 8:12PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 812 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Indian Mountain, or 27 miles south of McCall, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Indian Mountain and northern Cascade Reservoir around 820 PM MDT.
Tamarack Ski Area around 830 PM MDT.
Donnelly around 840 PM MDT.
Paddy Flat Work Center around 850 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
